  {
    "id": 1621359391868,
    "type": "text",
    "content": "\"<h1>Condition</h1>\""
  },
  {
    "id": 1637015624298,
    "type": "grid",
    "content": [
      [
        {
          "id": 1637015628543,
          "type": "text",
          "content": "\"<h2>Live Hard Coral Cover</h2><p>Prior to 1998, the modelled average live hard coral cover in the Pacific was relatively high and stable, ranging between 37.0% and 37.7%. Since 1998, there has been a general decline in live hard coral cover corresponding with global-scale coral bleaching events in 1998, 2014, 2015 and 2016. These successive bleaching events provided limited opportunity for corals to recover between events, except between 2009 and 2011. Coral loss accelerated between 2015 and 2017, declining to 31.3% in 2019.</p>\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "id": 1637015709056,
          "type": "text",
          "content": "\"<h2>Algae Cover</h2><p>Algal cover has been increasing in the Pacific over the past 15 years from 12% in 2004, to 16% in 2014, with a steeper increase to 20% in 2019, mirroring the decline in live hard coral cover.</p>\""
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
